description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a full time Band 6 post in the Occupational Therapy service within Ablett Psychiatric Unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, motivated and experienced Occupational Therapist who is passionate about working within acute mental health services, working primarily with adults with complex mental health issues. You will work collaboratively with the multidisciplinary team offering assessments, creating care &amp; treatment plans and implementing appropriate interventions. The post holder will be required to work independently and liaise with a variety of agencies and third sector organisations plus the individual’s carers and family members.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have excellent communication skills, have the ability to build and maintain effective working relationships, be self-motivated, proactive, and demonstrate a commitment to excellent service delivery and evidence based clinical practice. You must be approachable, compassionate, hardworking, and be able to manage your time effectively. The candidate should also have a proven history of providing supervision to junior staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate should be enthusiastic about your own professional development. They will receive support in their new role and will be encouraged in further career development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 12th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Gaynor Gaskell&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Clinical Lead Occupational Therapist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: Gaynor.V.Gaskell@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 07796337506&lt;/p&gt;
